title: Abderrahmane Benbouzid — Wikipédia
snippet: Abderrahmane Benbouzid (en arabe : عبد الرحمان بن بوزيد), né le 1er juin 1950 à Ouled Djellal, est un médecin et un homme politique algérien.

title: Abderrahmane Benbouzid
snippet: ALGIERS- The minister of Health, Abderrahmane Benbouzid, on Monday stressed the commitment of Algeria, in coordination with Arab countries, to promoting health in the Arab world.

title: Meaning of the name Benbouzid
snippet: Several notable individuals bear the name Benbouzid. One prominent example is Bouzid Benbouzid, an Algerian politician who served as the Minister of National Education. He was born on December 2, 1952, and is known for his significant role in shaping Algeria's education policies and reforms ...
